                "actions": {
                    "value": ""
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>To put Chandriu to rest permanently, a hero must convince her to stop pining over Volluk with a successful <span data-pf2-check=\"diplomacy\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"divine,necromancy\" data-pf2-label=\"Convince Chandriu DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Diplomacy</span> check.</p>\n<p data-visibility=\"gm\">Regardless of the result of this check, Chandriu flies into a rage and attacks, but if the Diplomacy check is successful, she is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 10 rounds while she fights. If defeated while she is slowed, she is put to rest.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a ghost is destroyed, it re-forms after [[/br 2d4 #days]]{2d4 days} within the location it's bound to, fully healed. A ghost can be permanently destroyed only if someone determines the reason for its existence and sets right whatever prevents the spirit from resting.</p>"
                },
